  "prompt": "Is it normal to have no dreams while sleeping?",
  "response": "Yes, it is normal for some people to not remember their dreams or to feel like they do not dream at all. Dreaming occurs during the REM (rapid eye movement) stage of sleep, and while everyone typically experiences REM sleep multiple times per night, not all individuals remember their dreams upon waking. Factors such as sleep quality, stress, medication, and individual differences in brain activity can influence dream recall. If you consistently don't remember any dreams and are concerned about your sleep, it might be a good idea to consult a healthcare professional.",
